data.title: Songs Dixie Land by Frank Stanton
data.meta_description: Songs From Dixie Land Classic Reprint by Frank L. Stanton and a great selection of related books, art and collectibles available now at AbeBooks.com.
data.text:
LeatherBound. Condition: New. LeatherBound edition. Condition: New. Reprinted from 1900 edition. Leather Binding on Spine and Corners with Golden leaf printing on spine. NO changes have been made to the original text. This is NOT a retyped or an ocr'd reprint. Illustrations, Index, if any, are included in black and white. Each page is checked manually before printing. As this print on demand book is reprinted from a very old book, there could be some missing or flawed pages, but we always try to make the book as complete as possible. Fold-outs, if any, are not part of the book. If the original book was published in multiple volumes then this reprint is of only one volume, not the whole set. Sewing binding for longer life, where the book block is actually sewn (smythe sewn/section sewn) with thread before binding which results in a more durable type of binding. Pages: 271 Language: English.

Hardcover. Condition: Near Fine. Bound in blue buckram with bright gilt titles and decoration to spine and front cover. Top page ends also bright gilt. Spine is age-toned to dark blue, some light foxing here and there to pages, no other defects. Binding is tight, pages are clean and unmarked. . A handsome copy. More than 100 songs of the South, lyrics only. . 8vo 8" - 9" tall. 239 pages. E6.

Hardcover. Condition: Very Good. Gallaway, W. H. (illustrator). Signed and inscribed by Georgia's first poet laureate, Frank L. Stanton, on the first free end page. Text and images are unmarked; pages are bright, though the page edges are age toned. Previous owner's plate glued to the front pastedown. The front pastedown also has a ghost of the signature and inscription. Binding is tight and square. Covers show a little wear around the corners and at the head and base of the spine. Covers are lightly foxed and the spine is just a little faded. No dust jacket. 239pp. Inscribed by Author.
